The paper deals with the construction of locality-sensitive hash functions, which is a topic in computer science that falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the efficiency of the new construction, which involves analyzing the expected number of hash collisions, a topic that falls under information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper mentions the application of LSH-based similarity search in computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Therefore, these are the five most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
